          <p class="c6 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p>
          <p class="c6">
            <span class="c25"
              >====== From the Tribute Book (placed at the memorial next to
              Jing&rsquo;s office)<br /></span
            ><span class="c4"
              >Jing, you were a great friend. I&rsquo;m going to miss you a lot.
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c6 c5"><span class="c4"></span></p>
          <p class="c6"><span class="c4">Hey Jing, </span></p>
          <p class="c6">
            <span class="c4"
              >I can still hear you yelling &ldquo;Hey Boat&rdquo; after passing
              by my office. It is hard to believe my last interaction was at the
              CITA lounge, calmly telling folks at CITA who were looking for new
              jobs you were going to stick around Toronto, because you liked it
              here so much. I will miss you.
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c4">&ndash; J. J. Zanazzi</span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c4"></span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c4"
              >To the best line dancer I know, I will miss you my friend!
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c4">&ndash; Jacob Taylor</span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c4"></span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c4"
              >Hola Jing, thanks for all your help and support during these
              years. I couldn&rsquo;t have done it without you! You will be
              missed but you&rsquo;ll always live in my heart</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c26">&ndash; </span
            ><span class="c3">Tom&aacute;s Cassanelli</span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Hey Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >Sorry I can&rsquo;t bother you about pulsar timing and you
              can&rsquo;t bother me about plasma lensing anymore. I hope you
              find more diamonds on the other side.</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">&ndash; Fangxi Lin</span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Hey Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >Thank you for all your patience explaining PINT and ATNF. Your
              enthusiasm is so contagious and made everything exciting!
              I&rsquo;ll miss hearing your voice in the office and your constant
              jokes. Howdy, Rocket Cowboy
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3">&ndash; Ashley Stock&#x1f680;</span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >The 12th floor of MP won&rsquo;t be the same without you.
              I&rsquo;ll never forget your kindness, generosity and enthusiasm.
              Thank you so much for always making everyone feel included, for
              always being such a generous host, for coming to check in and
              spend time with me in the early days of the pandemic, and for
              always being a wonderful friend. I&rsquo;m sorry there are so many
              things we never got to do and I&rsquo;ll miss you so much.
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3">&ndash; Emily Deibert &#9825;</span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >Jing, you are such a kind, wonderful and bright person with a
              generous and caring heart. You are deeply missed. &#x1f31f;</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">&ndash; Jennifer Chan </span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Hi Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >Thanks for being such a lively presence on MP 12th floor. It was
              always a delight to chat with you and I wish we could do that
              more. Will miss you a lot.
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">&ndash; Eesha</span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Dear Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >CITA feels so much more empty without you around. Your warm
              presence was such a gift to everyone, and I&rsquo;m very glad we
              had a chance to meet.
            </span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Safe travels,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3">&ndash; Dylan &#21608;&#24535;&#25562;</span>
          </p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Hi Jing,</span></p>
          <p class="c2">
            <span class="c3"
              >Thank you so much for all the happiness and smiles you brought to
              CITA. It was a very welcoming place because of you, and
              we&rsquo;ll all always be thankful for having worked here with
              you!</span
            >
          </p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">All the best,</span></p>
          <p class="c2"><span class="c3">Nate Carlson</span></p>
          <p class="c2 c5"><span class="c3"></span></p>
